data.text:
WHAT IT IS: This rising U.K. artist cracked the Official U.K. Singles chart with her breakout single, “labour,” a rallying cry against misogyny that struck a nerve with women around the globe. The song has generated 170m+ streams, contributing to her 300m+ career streams, leading to her TV debut on The Kelly Clarkson Show. She was named to Spotify’s Juniper Artist to Watch 2024, tapped as a Spotify Equal Ambassador and is a YouTube Trending Artist on the Rise. The songstress was also picked as an Amazon Music Breakthrough Artist to Watch 2024. Her debut album, Cacophony, is set for release on 8/30.ALBUM: Cacophony

RELEASE DATE: 8/30

SINGLE: “labour”

TV: Kelly Clarkson

LIVE: Sold out debut U.S. headline tour starting 6/12 in major markets; performing at Reading and Leeds festival; previously played Bonnaroo 2023 and supported Maisie Peters in the U.K./Europe

INTERNET: 4m+ monthly Spotify listeners; viral reaction with over 1.1b views and 70k video creations on “labour”; up 100k followers (last month) on TikTok; 200m+ combined YouTube views

PRESS: Rolling Stone (“Songs You Need to Know), NME, Dork, DIY, The Independent, Wonderland, Ones to Watch, more

BOOKING: Mike Marquis/CAA

MANAGEMENT: Josh Sanger/DEEP END
